## 1. Task Intent Interpretation

### 1.1 Problem Summary

NuttyFans has a comprehensive UI/UX Blueprint but the design system is not implemented in code:

| What Exists | What's Missing |
|-------------|----------------|
| Color palette in docs | CSS variables in code |
| Typography scale in docs | Tailwind theme extension |
| Spacing system in docs | Design tokens as code |
| Component specs in docs | Actual React components |
| Tailwind CSS installed | Custom theme configuration |
| Empty `src/components/ui/` | Reusable UI components |

### 1.2 Business Value

| Benefit | Impact |
|---------|--------|
| **Development Speed** | Reusable components reduce dev time by 40-60% |
| **Consistency** | Single source of truth for UI |
| **Maintainability** | Change once, update everywhere |
| **Accessibility** | shadcn/ui components are WCAG compliant |
| **Designer-Dev Alignment** | Same tokens = same language |

---

## 2. Research: Design System Patterns

### 2.1 Industry Best Practices

| Practice | Description | NuttyFans Approach |
|----------|-------------|-------------------|
| **Design Tokens** | Abstract values (colors, spacing) as variables | CSS variables + Tailwind |
| **Component Composition** | Small components compose into larger ones | shadcn/ui pattern |
| **Accessibility First** | WCAG 2.1 AA compliance | shadcn/ui + Radix UI |
| **Dark Mode Ready** | CSS variables enable theme switching | Prepare variables |
| **Type Safety** | Props typed with TypeScript | All components typed |

### 2.2 shadcn/ui vs Alternatives

| Factor | shadcn/ui | Radix UI | Chakra UI | Material UI |
|--------|-----------|----------|-----------|-------------|
| Customization | ✅ Full control | ✅ Unstyled | 🟡 Theme-based | 🟡 Theme-based |
| Bundle Size | ✅ Only what you use | ✅ Minimal | ❌ Large | ❌ Large |
| Copy-paste model | ✅ Own the code | ❌ Install pkg | ❌ Install pkg | ❌ Install pkg |
| Tailwind Native | ✅ Yes | ❌ Manual | ❌ No | ❌ No |
| Accessibility | ✅ Radix-based | ✅ Native | ✅ Good | ✅ Good |
| Next.js 15 | ✅ Compatible | ✅ Compatible | 🟡 Some issues | 🟡 Some issues |

**Decision: shadcn/ui** — Already specified in tech architecture, best fit for Tailwind + Next.js.

